  "doc_id": "17161",
  "text": "A summary of the currently ongoing trials can be found in Table 2 [CITATION_1] . These studies include gene therapy approaches using interleukin 13 and suicide genes; gene vaccination using plasmid DNA; and oncolytic viral gene therapy for pancreatic cancer, metastatic pancreatic cancer, pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor, and pancreatitis. In addition, cell therapies, including CAR-T for adoptive immunotherapy, are being evaluated in clinical trials. This system is considered as an adoptive active immunotherapy and autologous CD8 positive T cells are extracted from the patients and modified ex vivo to recognize and kill the cancer cells expressing the tumor antigen. There are more than 20 clinical trials still recruiting the candidate for the trials and newer trials will start continuously to develop the safe and effective gene therapy for the pancreatic diseases.",
